entry.title: MiraclePtr: Mark performance-sensitive containers
entry.content:
Both `cc::LayerImplList` and `cc::RenderSurfaceList` are visible in

stack samples when we enable Renderer BRP (and when these types are

vectors of `raw_ptr`s).



This CL keeps them unrewritten (i.e. keeps them as vectors of raw

pointers) but directly attaches `RAW_PTR_EXCLUSION` to the usage sites,

as that's the only real way to make the rewriter ignore them.

entry.title: [Office fallback] Flip around include_task_in_reason_message usage
entry.content:
Previously the usage of include_task_in_reason_message led to the right

dialogs getting the task included in the reason message but the variable

name didn't make sense.



When include_task_in_reason_message was true, the task was not included

in the reason message. When it was false, the task was included.



Since the include_task_in_reason_message was also set the wrong was

around for each fallback reason, this double negative gave a positive

so the task was included for the right fallback reasons.



Use the include_task_in_reason_message consistently.

entry.title: Stop occlusion tracking from being unpaused during overview animation
entry.content:
When overview mode exits, OverviewGrid::EndScroll is called, via a

destructor, which cancels the pause of the occlusion tracker. If it

takes longer for the overview mode animation to complete than the pause

time here (0.5 seconds), then the occlusion tracker can be unpaused

before the animation ends. Normally, it will be unpaused by this

EndScroll() code but the animation will finish, and the unpause timer

will be reset to 0.5 seconds again at that point.



This CL adds a RAII guard, OcclusionPauser, for overview mode that

should be used for each separate type of sequence for pausing and

delaying the unpause of occlusion tracking. For example, OverviewGrid

needs to pause both for screen rotation and scrolling, so it should

create two OcclusionPauser objects to represent those two types of

events (assuming that a single type of event can not happen multiple

times at the same time).

entry.title: [SHv2] Fix backwards incompatibility with stored results
entry.content:
As part of crrev.com/c/5000387, the result that is stored in prefs was

simplified and minimized. For the result of unused site permissions,

this also resulted in the format of the stored Dict to be changed. As a

result, when updating, users would still have the older version of the

stored Dict while the code was expecting the new version, resulting in a

crash. This CL addresses this issue by checking whether the the data

format is still of an older version, or whether it is of a new one.

entry.title: [remoting] Apply text-scaling-factor for multiple monitors.
entry.content:
Before this CL, DesktopResizerX11 refused to set the

text-scaling-factor if multiple monitors were detected. But the logic

was flawed, because it counted the RANDR "connected" monitors, rather

than just the enabled monitors.



This CL addresses this by setting the text-scaling-factor even if

there are multiple monitors. This is possible because GNOME's X11

backend enforces each monitor to have the same scale - so the

calculation would give correct results for all monitors.



Bug: b:326598074

entry.title: webauthn: handle internal transitions in `StateMachine` differently.
entry.content:
In order to allow an internal transition, without an external event,

from any state to `kNextAction`, `Loop` loops and creates `None` events

as needed. Every state other than `kNextAction` needs to ignore the

these `None` events.



Since the only internal transition is to `kNextAction`, handle that

specially. The previous way seems a little conceptually cleaner in my

mind, but it's not worth the overhead.



Now, since `Loop` doesn't loop any longer, rename it to `Process`.

entry.content:
This roll includes several fixes needed to unblock the automated roll.

In particular, the biggest change is disabling Abseil support in

GoogleTest: GoogleTest has switched to using Abseil flags when

GTEST_HAS_ABSL is set, which is incompatible with Chrome. For Chrome,

the main impact of disabling Abseil support is losing the pretty printer

for absl::variant; however, Chrome plans to switch to std::variant once

the codegen issues are fixed.



Unfortunately, this also requires suppressing GN check for GoogleTest

to prevent errors from false positives, since GN does not understand

conditional includes and does not realize that the Abseil flags headers

are not actually included.
